{"word":"H8446 - תּוּר - tûwr - toor - Chap","slug":"H8446","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">תּוּר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>tûwr"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>toor"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Chap"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05EA;&#x05BC;&#x05D5;&#x05BC;&#x05E8; - tu&#x0302;r</b> - <i>toor</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>meander</i> (causatively <i>guide</i>) about, especially for trade or reconnoitring: - chap [-man], sent to descry, be excellent, merchant [-man], search (out), seek, (e-) spy (out)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3491\">H3491</a>, <a href=\"#/H8447\">H8447</a>, <a href=\"#/H8448\">H8448</a>"}]}